{
    "Body": " Location: San Francisco, CA Coinbase has built the world's leading compliant cryptocurrency platform serving over 30 million accounts in more than 100 countries. With multiple successful products, and our vocal advocacy for blockchain technology, we have played a major part in mainstream awareness and adoption of cryptocurrency. We are proud to offer an entire suite of products that are helping build the cryptoeconomy, and increase economic freedom around the world. There are a few things we look for across all hires we make at Coinbase, regardless of role or team. First, we assess whether a candidate demonstrates our values: Clear Communication, Positive Energy, Efficient Execution, and Continuous Learning. Second, we look for signals that a candidate will thrive in a culture like ours, where we default to trust, embrace feedback, disrupt ourselves, and expect sustained high performance because we play as a championship team. Finally, we seek people with the desire and capacity to build and share expertise in the frontier technologies of crypto and blockchain, in whatever way is most relevant to their role. Read more about our values and culture here. We are building a Client Platform Engineering / System Engineering team to scale and secure our enterprise environment. We focus on automation, tooling, and processes managed by IT while also investing in open source solutions for our future endpoint fleet. This role works across the global IT organization while also partnering closely with Security to improve engineering processes, build and develop best practices, and deliver technology solutions that enable the business. We are looking for individuals to help contribute and build the Client Platform / System Engineering team as the company scales, enabling world class deliverables to meet the challenge of a dynamic, fast-paced environment focused on positive impact. What You'll Be Doing Collaborate with your team to spearhead end-to-end process design, improvements, automation and management of the fleets. Balance security and usability with an automation focused approach to fleet management. Provide durable and optimized services for internal applications. Ensure high availability across all backing services. Help ensure the security and usability of all personal computing at Coinbase. Lead and create technical documentation and procedures to improve existing process gaps. Act as an ambassador and change agent to build a culture of continuous improvement, blame free post-mortems, SLAs, and deliver towards an infrastructure as code environment. Mentor and collaborate with lower level engineers and grow the capabilities of your team. What We Look For In You Enterprise experience with fleet management with a focus on automation. BS/MS in Computer Science or equivalent practical experience. Excellent collaboration, communication and mentoring skills. You have deep experience with Chef, Puppet, Ansible, JAMF, OSQuery, Munki, Santa, and/or other similar tools.. Experience in MacOS system provisioning and thin imaging (e.g. DEP and ABM Apple Business Manager). Experience building and maintaining production systems Hands-on coding/scripting ability Nice To Haves Interest or passion for building solid, scalable infrastructure Experience using Amazon Web Services, Google Compute Engine, Kinesis, Postgres, MongoDB and Redis or similar. Experience deploying, integrating & securing service discovery What To Send Links to your GitHub/Stack Overflow or something awesome that you've built A brief answer to the following question: What have you built that you\u2019re most proud of? A resume or LinkedIn profile Coinbase is committed to diversity in its workforce and is proud to be an equal opportunity employer and to review all of our job postings to minimize biased language. Coinbase does not make hiring or employment decisions on the basis of race, color, religion, creed, gender, national origin, age, disability, veteran status, marital status, pregnancy, sex, gender expression or identity, sexual orientation, citizenship, or any other basis protected by applicable local, state or federal law. Coinbase will also consider for employment qualified applicants with arrest and conviction records in a manner consistent with San Francisco\u2019s Fair Chance Ordinance and similar local laws. Global Data Privacy Notice for Job Candidates and Applicants Depending on your location, the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) and California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA) may regulate the way we manage the data of job applicants. Our full notice outlining how your data will be processed as part of the application procedure for application locations is available here: Ireland/EU, United Kingdom, and California. By submitting your application, you are agreeing to our use and processing of your data as required. ", 
